  "response": "According to the Bible, Adam and Eve lived in the Garden of Eden. The Garden of Eden is described in the Book of Genesis as a paradise created by God that contained the Tree of Life and the Tree of Knowledge of Good and Evil. The exact location of the Garden of Eden has been a subject of speculation and debate, with some interpretations suggesting it might have been located near the Tigris and Euphrates rivers in present-day Iraq, but its precise location is not known and is often considered a theological concept rather than a historical or geographical fact.",
